<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I sometimes write =E2=80=9Ceverything is secur=
ities fraud=E2=80=9D as a shorthand for a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/34519830.285376/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMDMvZ29sZG1hbi1zYWNocy1nb2VzLXRvLXN1cHJlbW=
UtY291cnQtaGVkZ2UtZnVuZHMtd29uLW9uLWdhbWVzdG9wLWtrcG9lNndzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyM=
jkyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0=
bV90ZXJtPTI0MDIyOSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
Bee2138d2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">  particular weird argument</a> about how modern US lega=
l dynamics transmute every bad action taken by a public company into securi=
ties fraud, but never mind that. A simpler story is that if the board of di=
rectors of a company (public or private) puts out a public statement saying=
 =E2=80=9Cturns out our chief executive officer is a big liar,=E2=80=9D=C2=
=A0<em>somebody=C2=A0</em>is going to think that=E2=80=99s securities fraud=
. Whatever the CEO was lying about was=C2=A0<em>probably=C2=A0</em>material=
 to the company =E2=80=94=C2=A0otherwise why would the board care? =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0and you=E2=80=99ve got to at least look into it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This isn=E2=80=99t quite that, but=C2=A0<a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34519830.285376/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS90ZWNoL3NlYy1pbnZlc3RpZ2F0aW5nLXdoZXRoZXItb3BlbmFpLWludmV=
zdG9ycy13ZXJlLW1pc2xlZC05ZDkwYjQxMT9tb2Q9aHBfbGVhZF9wb3Mx/607f07ceef4b8524a=
319a23cBd9c79853" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">the Wall Street Journal reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission is scru=
tinizing internal communications by OpenAI Chief Executive Sam Altman as pa=
rt of an investigation into whether the company=E2=80=99s investors were mi=
sled.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The regulator, whose probe hasn=E2=80=99t prev=
iously been reported, has been seeking internal records from current and fo=
rmer OpenAI officials and directors, and sent a subpoena to OpenAI in Decem=
ber, according to people familiar with the matter. That followed the OpenAI=
 board=E2=80=99s decision in November to fire Altman as CEO and oust him fr=
om the board. At the time, directors said Altman hadn=E2=80=99t been =E2=80=
=9Cconsistently candid in his communications,=E2=80=9D but didn=E2=80=99t e=
laborate. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Some of the people familiar with the investiga=
tion described it as a predictable response to the former OpenAI board=E2=
=80=99s claim in its November statement. One of the people said that the SE=
C hasn=E2=80=99t pointed to any specific statement or communication by Altm=
an that it has deemed misleading.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Right, maybe they=E2=80=99ll find a =E2=80=9Cs=
pecific statement or communication=E2=80=9D=C2=A0<em>to investors=C2=A0</em=
>that was misleading, and he=E2=80=99ll get in trouble; probably they won=
=E2=80=99t.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-8" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-c=
olor: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[8]</span>
</a> But if the board of directors of a giant company fires the CEO for the=
 stated reason that he was=C2=A0<em>not candid</em>, the SEC really does ha=
ve to look into it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CA giant company,=E2=80=9D I said; not=
 necessarily a <em>public=C2=A0</em>one. =E2=80=9CThe SEC enforces laws tha=
t forbid people from misleading investors, regardless of whether fundraiser=
s seek capital in public or private markets,=E2=80=9D notes the Journal, co=
rrectly. Still there are some relevant differences between OpenAI and most =
companies:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">OpenAI=E2=80=99s stock does not conti=
nuously trade in public markets, so its CEO could go around lying about lot=
s of stuff without=C2=A0<em>tricking investors into buying stock</em>. If y=
ou are the CEO of a public company and you go on television and say =E2=80=
=9Cwe have built a superintelligent robot that can cure cancer,=E2=80=9D pe=
ople will buy your stock, the stock will go up, and if it turns out you wer=
e lying, they will sue you for fraud. If you are the CEO of a private compa=
ny and you do that, nobody will trade the stock, because they can=E2=80=99t=
. If you then try to raise money by selling stock to investors two weeks la=
ter, and you send them a private placement memo saying =E2=80=9Cwe have not=
 built a superintelligent robot, we=E2=80=99re not even working on cancer, =
our CEO was just letting off steam on TV,=E2=80=9D and then they buy the st=
ock, they weren=E2=80=99t misled, were they? This is very much not legal ad=
vice, don=E2=80=99t do it, but the point is that=C2=A0<em>every public stat=
ement=C2=A0</em>by a public-company CEO is risky, while private companies h=
ave more limited investment-related communications.</li>=09<li style=3D"mar=
gin-bottom: 5px;">In a typical=C2=A0<em>private=C2=A0</em>company, and part=
icularly in a typical=C2=A0<em>tech startup</em>, if the CEO is lying to th=
e board of directors, he is also lying to his investors, because ordinarily=
 the board will include several representatives of the venture capital firm=
s that invest in the business. So if the board feels misled, the investors =
probably feel misled, because they=E2=80=99re the same people. That's not t=
he case here. In fact, it is exactly the opposite here: OpenAI=E2=80=99s <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34519830.285376/aHR0=
cHM6Ly9vcGVuYWkuY29tL291ci1zdHJ1Y3R1cmU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB529cff7d" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;">=09description of its corporate structure</a> says =E2=80=9Cthe boa=
rd remains majority independent,=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cindependent director=
s do not hold equity in OpenAI.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0(Microsoft Corp., OpenAI=E2=
=80=99s biggest investor, is represented by=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34519830.285376/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJn=
LmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMDUvbWljcm9zb2Z0LXBpY2tzLWRlZS10ZW1wbGV=
0b24tYXMtb3BlbmFpLWJvYXJkLW9ic2VydmVyP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMjkyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJn=
V0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDIyOSZ1d=
G1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe48fcef4" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
an observer on the board</a>, but has no voting rights, and even the observ=
er seat came after Altman=E2=80=99s firing and unfiring.) So in some sense =
the board of directors was a good group for Altman to mislead: They weren=
=E2=80=99t investors!</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">I continue t=
o find it funny and relevant that, at the top of <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34519830.285376/aHR0cHM6Ly9vcGVuYWkuY29tL291=
ci1zdHJ1Y3R1cmU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC529cff7d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> OpenAI=E2=80=99=
s operating agreement</a>, it warns investors: =E2=80=9CIt would be wise to=
 view any investment in OpenAI Global, LLC in the spirit of a donation, wit=
h the understanding that it may be difficult to know what role money will p=
lay in a post-[artificial general intelligence] world.=E2=80=9D I still don=
=E2=80=99t know what Altman was supposedly not candid about, but whatever i=
t was, how material can it possibly have been=C2=A0<em>to investors</em>, g=
iven what they signed up for? =E2=80=9COoh he said it cost $50 million to t=
rain this model but it was really $53 million=E2=80=9D or whatever, come on=
, the investors were donating money, they=E2=80=99re not sweating the detai=
ls.</li>
</ol>
