ask, and the chief financial officer might say =E2=80=9Csure, what happened=
 there is ...=E2=80=9D and try to give some further explanation of the numb=
ers that investors care about.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And also there is, sometimes, a third thing, w=
here investors can call up the company=E2=80=99s investor-relations officer=
s directly and say =E2=80=9CI am trying to update my model, I see that reve=
nue in the widgets segment is up 2% but margins have contracted, can you he=
lp me understand,=E2=80=9D and the IR officers might give the investor a bi=
t more explanation. Or they might not. The IR officers have to balance thei=
r desire to be helpful =E2=80=94=C2=A0the investors own the company, and th=
e IR officers=E2=80=99 job is to help them understand it =E2=80=94=C2=A0wit=
h their desire for fairness; the IR officers are not supposed to tell one i=
nvestor secret material information that the other investors don=E2=80=99t =
know. (This is both a matter of=C2=A0<em>good investor relations </em>and=
=C2=A0also a legal requirement; in the US, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
